<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Ontology> .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#imports> <http://purl.org/family/> .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#imports> <http://purl.org/meo/> .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#imports> <http://purl.org/story/event/> .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#imports> <http://purl.org/story/location/> .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#imports> <http://purl.org/story/social/> .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#imports> <http://www.w3.org/2006/time#> .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#imports> <https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An ontology for the Region Connection Calculus."@en .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Classes and properties for the narrated structure of a story, such as stories, chapters and climaxes, and how they relate to events."@en .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Events with their participants, locations and temporal ordering, using the W3C Time ontology to describe time."@en .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Intentional doings: agents, patients, instruments, themes; linked to events via sub-event links and participant entailments."@en .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Non-familial social ties between characters, such as allegiance, enmity or membership in a house or group."@en .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Places and spatial relations that are relevant for describing a story plot."@en .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Story intervals use Allen's endpoints Is and Ie via stime:hasStart and stime:hasEnd on top of the W3C Time ontology.\r\n\r\nThe thirteen Allen relations (b, bi, m, mi, o, oi, s, si, d, di, f, fi, eq) are not redefined here: use the corresponding OWL-Time object properties between time:ProperInterval individuals — time:intervalBefore (b), time:intervalAfter (bi), time:intervalMeets (m), time:intervalMetBy (mi), time:intervalOverlaps (o), time:intervalOverlappedBy (oi), time:intervalStarts (s), time:intervalStartedBy (si), time:intervalDuring (d), time:intervalContains (di), time:intervalFinishes (f), time:intervalFinishedBy (fi), time:intervalEquals (eq).\r\n\r\ntime:intervalOverlaps (Allen o) is not symmetric: the inverse is time:intervalOverlappedBy (oi). Do not model story 'overlaps' as a symmetric relation.\r\n\r\nstime:StoryTimeInterval is a proper interval so those relations (domain/range ProperInterval in OWL Time) apply when asserting temporal structure between story intervals. Below, sound property chains link endpoint ordering (time:before / time:after on instants) to intervalBefore / intervalAfter."@en .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Actions in story plots"@en .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Allen-style time for story plots"@en .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Events and temporal relations in stories"@en .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Locations for story plots"@en .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Narrative structure of stories"@en .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Social relations in stories"@en .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "The RCC8 ontology" .
