<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/ntppi> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "the first region entirely contains the second region and their boundaries do not touch"@en .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/ntppi> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "non-tangential proper part inverse"@en .
# 
# https://purl.org/region/rcc8/po
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/po> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/po> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#SymmetricProperty> .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/po> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#IrreflexiveProperty> .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/po> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://purl.org/region/rcc8/Region> .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/po> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://purl.org/region/rcc8/Region> .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/po> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "the two regions partially overlap (there are disjoint sub parts, and some part of one is included in some part of the other"@en .
<https://purl.org/region/rcc8/po> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "partially overlapping"@en .
# 
# https://purl.org/region/rcc8/tpp
